{"lemma":"قَيْظِ","slug":"قَيْظِ","root":"ق.#.ظ","root_slug":"ق-_-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-_-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n36484"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"midsummer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intense heat"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *qayθ̣- (“summer”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *ḳayč̣- (“to be hot; summer”). Cognate with Aramaic קֵיטָא (qēṭā) and Hebrew קַיִץ (káyits, qáyiṣ)."},"ipa":["/qajðˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36484","headword_ar":"قَيْظٌ","root":"qyZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense, heat of summer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of the Pleiades,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, at the commencement of the era of the Flight, was about the 13th of May, O. S.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of Canopus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, at the same period, was about the 4th of August, O. S.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intenseness, of heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoyaAZN","text_ar":"اَقْيَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quyuwZN","text_ar":"قُيُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Also, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter which people"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commonly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"call the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summerquarter, commencing when the sun enters the sign of Cancer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so termed by some, who called the spring-quarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the autumnal-quarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; others [in later times] calling the summer-quarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syof","text_ar":"صيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":", the spring-quarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the autumnal-quarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but agreeing with the former in calling the winterquarter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='","text_ar":"شِتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mir-át ez-Zemán:) the Arabs say, that the year consists of four seasons, every one of these being three months; namely, the quarter called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is that called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkalaA_i","text_ar":"الكَلَاـِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", consisting of [the Syrian months] Ádhár and Neysán and Eiyár [or March and April and May, O. S.]; then, the quarter called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":", consisting of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hazeerán and Temmooz and Áb"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"June and July and August, O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"]; then, the quarter called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", consisting of Eylool and the two Tishreens [or September and October and November, O. S.]; and then, the quarter called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='","text_ar":"شِتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", consisting of the two Kánoons and Shubát [or December and January and February, O. S.]. (Az, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taquwmu Als~aAEapu","text_ar":"لَا تَقُومُ السَّاعَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY yakuwna Alwaladu gayoZFA wAlmaTaru qayoZFA","text_ar":"حَتَّى يَكُونَ الوَلَدُ غَيْظًا والمَطَرُ قَيْظًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying of Mohammad, meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The resurrection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the time thereof, will not come to pass until the"},{"kind":"text","text":"birth of a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child be"},{"kind":"text","text":"an occasion of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rage, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain be"},{"kind":"text","text":"accompanied by air like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qyZ","text_ar":"قيظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most vehement heat of summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijotamaEa","text_ar":"اـِجْتَمَعَ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2580},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqayoZu","text_ar":"القَيْظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an elliptical and abridged phrase, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men, assembled themselves in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}